doc.previous: Each article and each user of Wikipedia has an associated "Talk" page. These form the primary communication channel for editors to discuss, coordinate and debate.[60]
doc.after: Wikipedia's community has been described as cult-like,[61] although not always with entirely negative connotations.[62] The project's preference for cohesiveness, even if it requires compromise that includes disregard of credentials, has been referred to as "anti-elitism".[63]
